Purpose of Processing
Lawful Basis for Processing


Consent


Register and administer your membership in our Site
If you have an account with us, we have your consent to process your personal data for a specific purpose. Your consent may be revoked at any time.

Processing is necessary for our legitimate interests and cannot be reasonably achieved by other, less intrusive means.


Provide customer service and support
Processing is necessary for our legitimate interests and cannot be reasonably achieved by other, less intrusive means.


Verify communications from you
Processing is necessary for our legitimate interests and cannot be reasonably achieved by other, less intrusive means.


Disclose information to third parties in order to:

establish, defend or exercise our legal rights;
protect or defend the Site, users, or our subsidiaries and affiliates, and all of their respective officers, directors, employees, attorneys, agents, contractors, licensors, and partners, in connection with any actual or alleged legal action, claim or dispute;
respond to claims that any posting or other content of our Site violates the rights of third parties;
in an emergency, to protect the health and safety of our Site's users or the general public; or
to third-party service providers to provide technical functionality on our behalf.
 
Processing is necessary for our legitimate interests and cannot be reasonably achieved by other, less intrusive means.

Processing is necessary for our legitimate interests and cannot be reasonably achieved by other, less intrusive means.


Enforce our Terms of Service and contracts with third parties
Processing is necessary for our legitimate interests and cannot be reasonably achieved by other, less intrusive means.


Prevent fraud and other prohibited or illegal activities or to otherwise comply with applicable laws and regulations
Processing is necessary for our legitimate interests and cannot be reasonably achieved by other, less intrusive means.


Compliance with Legal Obligations


 Disclose information to third parties in order to:

comply with a court order, search warrant, subpoena, or other legal process;
to comply with legal, regulatory or administrative requirements of any governmental authorities; or
otherwise fulfill a government or law enforcement request for information.
 
Processing is necessary to comply with a legal obligation.
